c: 7
v: 195
t: "Are for them feet (legs) they walk with it, or (are) for them hands they destroy/attack violently with it, or (are) for them eyes/sights they see/understand with it, or (are) for them ears, they hear/listen with it? Say: \"Call your partners (with God) then plot/conspire against me , so you (will) not delay me/give me time"